results.name: n^3 - A065733(n).
comment: a(n) = 0 for n = m^2. - _Zak Seidov_, May 11 2007

It has been asked whether some primes do not occur in this sequence. It seems indeed that primes 3, 5, 17, 23, 29, 31, 37, 41, 43, 59, 61,... do not occur, primes 2, 7, 11, 13, 19, 47, 53, 67, 79, 83,... do. For further investigations, see A087285 = the range of this sequence, and also the related sequences A229618 = range of A181138, and A165288. - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 26 2013 and Oct 05 2013
formula: a(n) = A154333(n) unless n is a square or, equivalently, a(n)=0. - _M. F. Hasler_, Oct 05 2013
example: A065733(10) = 961 = 31^2 is the largest square less than or equal to 10^3 = 1000, therefore a(10) = 1000 - 961 = 39.
mathematica: Table[c = n^3; c - Floor[Sqrt[c]]^2, {n, 0, 200}] (* _Vladimir Joseph Stephan Orlovsky_, Jun 02 2011 *)
